  "faq": [
    {
      "q": "What AI model does ForgeOS use?",
      "a": "ForgeOS uses Claude (Anthropic) for gate intelligence, code review routing, and Shared Mind pattern recognition. AI costs are included in your plan — you are never charged separately for AI usage."
    },
    {
      "q": "Can I self-host ForgeOS?",
      "a": "Enterprise plans include dedicated infrastructure options. Contact enterprise@synctek.io for details."
    },
    {
      "q": "Is there a free trial?",
      "a": "Yes — all new accounts get a 14-day trial of all Pro features. No credit card required."
    },
    {
      "q": "How does the audit ledger work?",
      "a": "Every governance action (gate approval, review, changeset) is recorded in a hash-chained JSONL ledger signed with Ed25519 keys. Each entry's hash includes the previous entry, making the chain tamper-evident."
    },
    {
      "q": "What is the ForgeOS Trust Index (FTI)?",
      "a": "FTI is a context-aware trust scoring system for open-source packages. It evaluates packages across 8 dimensions (security, maintainability, documentation, community health, supply chain, improvement velocity, operational, governance) and provides scores tailored to your specific security posture, team size, and tech stack. FTI scoring is included with all ForgeOS plans. A standalone metered API is also available for AI agents and external integrations."
    },
    {
      "q": "How does FTI API pricing work?",
      "a": "FTI scoring is bundled with ForgeOS plans at your tier's API call limit. For standalone agentic access (without a ForgeOS subscription), metered pricing is available: $0.003/score for basic scoring, $0.005/score for recommendations, and $0.008/score for comparative analysis. Volume discounts available at 100K+ scores/month."
    }
  ],
